        <h1>Welcome to Team Schooly D IRC</h1>
        <p class="lead">The official IRC server of Team Schooly D and its affiliates</p>
        <h2>Get Connected!</h2>
        <p>
            IRC is an intense experience, and it's even more intense with Team Schooly D. While our
            <a href="http://teamschoolyd.org/chat/" target="_blank">web client</a> offers best-in-class service, it falls
            short of the stability and functionality of a dedicated IRC client. You can set yours up in just a few
            easy steps, start getting mad at video games with us in the time it takes to cook 3-minute rice!
        </p>
        <em>Power users can use the below information to connect. Normal folk can follow the steps below</em>
        <div class="well-sm">
            <samp>
                Server: irc.teamschoolyd.org<br/>
                Port: 6667<br/>
                SSL: No<br/>
                Channel: #tsd<br/>
            </samp>
        </div>
        <h3>Step 1</h3>
        <p>
            Download and install <a href="https://hexchat.github.io/" target="_blank">Hexchat</a>
            (or another IRC client of your choosing)
        </p>
        <h3>Step 2</h3>
        <p>
            <img src="https://hexchat.readthedocs.org/en/latest/_images/network_list.png"/>
            <br/>
            You should see the <strong>Network List</strong> when you start Hexchat.<br/>
            <strong>Nick name</strong> will be your handle in the chat. It should contain only letters, numbers, underscores,
            and hyphens (e.g. Schooly_D)<br/>
            <strong>Second</strong> and <strong>Third choice</strong> will be backup handles in case your first choice
            is already being used or unavailable (e.g. Schooly-D, SchoolyD)<br/>
            <strong>User name</strong> can be thought of as an "account name" or "login." Most other users will not see it, but it
            can be used for authentication and other purposes (e.g. schooly or schoolyd)
        </p>
        <h3>Step 3</h3>
        <p>
            <strong>Click the "Add" button on the right so we can add the TSD IRC server to your server list</strong>
            <br/>
            <img src="https://hexchat.readthedocs.org/en/latest/_images/network_list_edit.png"/>
            <br/>
            <strong>Replace the first server in the top list with: <samp>irc.teamschoolyd.org/6667</samp></strong><br/>
            Connect to selected server only: <strong>NO</strong><br/>
            Use global user information: <strong>YES</strong><br/>
            Auto connect to this network at startup: <strong>YES</strong><br/>
            Proxy server and SSL checkboxes: <strong>NO</strong><br/>
            Favorite channels: <strong>#tsd, #destiny</strong><br/>
            Click <strong>close</strong>
        </p>
        <h3>Step 4</h3>
        <p>
            Select TSDIRC from your server list and click <strong>Connect</strong>
        </p>
        <h3>Step 5</h3>
        <p>
            That's it! Enjoy your real-time communication and commiseration with esteemed TSD Associates
        </p>
